headline: The Score: Tesla, Capital One, Boeing and More Stocks That Defined the Week
summary: Elon Musk  is planning more time at  Tesla  less time in the White House.  During Tesla’s earnings call, the billionaire chief executive talked about his plans to pull back from the Department of Government Efficiency, saying that he expects to continue spending “a day or two” each week on government matters.  Musk’s controversial work with the Trump administration and his political endorsements have weighed on Tesla demand and led to protests and vandalism at Tesla showrooms.

headline: Capital One Financial (NYSE:COF) Reports Strong Q1 2025 Earnings
summary: Last week, Capital One Financial (NYSE:COF) experienced a notable 14% increase in its stock price. This price movement aligns with the company's strong Q1 2025 earnings report, which indicated a solid rise in net interest income and net income, despite an increase in net charge-offs. Meanwhile, the broader market also saw significant gains, with the S&P 500 up nearly 4% during the same period amid positive earnings reports and potential easing of tariffs. headline: Why Discover Financial Services Was Racing Higher This Week
summary: The past few days have been very eventful for Discover Financial Services (NYSE: DFS).  The company, best known as the entity behind the underdog Discover credit card, is now approved to be acquired by a peer.  With these strong winds at its back, according to data compiled by S&P Global Market Intelligence, Discover stock was up by more than 13% week to date as of very early Friday morning.

headline: Eastern Bank to broach Rhode Island with $490M HarborOne deal
summary: The transaction, set to close in the fourth quarter, would add 30 locations and $5.7 billion in assets to Eastern. The Boston bank has tended to expand through acquisition every two years.
